     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 
	 Friday Cat Photo: Flying Cats
	 </font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><div style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; display: inline; float: none; padding-top: 0px" id="scid:0767317B-992E-4b12-91E0-4F059A8CECA8:e2d13429-033a-408e-8cd1-207c49ea1dd8" class="wlWriterEditableSmartContent">Technorati Tags: <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/cats" rel="tag">cats</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/Friday+cat+photo" rel="tag">Friday cat photo</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/paper+bag" rel="tag">paper bag</a>, <a href="http://technorati.com/tags/rubber+stamp" rel="tag">rubber stamp</a></div> <p><a title="Flickr Photo: Flying Cats on a Paper Back" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/orcmid/4060179558/"><img style="margin: 5px auto; display: block; float: none" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2613/4060179558_95d916562c.jpg"></a> </p> <p>This image of flying cats came into our house on a paper bag from a local produce market.&nbsp; We have no idea what’s behind this.</p>  <div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div><p class="blogger-labels">Labels: <a rel='tag' href="http://orcmid.com/blog/labels/cats.asp">cats</a></p>
    </p>
